DeQoL LIFE - prelim descriptive results

Paul Schneider

2020-09-26


PRELIMINARY NOTES

  • Click on the ‘Code’ buttons on the right to view the source R code
  • Descriptive results for eq5d index and dimensions by imd, age, sex, and year
  • Sample: HSE 2003-2014
  • Participants >= 16 (because eq5d missing for children)
  • Participants >75 years were recoded to -> 75+ (because strata sizes too small)
  • Analysis based on 1-year age band data
  • 95% Confidence intervalls around mean estimates are bootstrapped with (only) 100 iterations
  • THERE SEEMS TO BE AN ISSUE WITH >1,500 PARTICPANTS HAVING AN EQ5D INDEX OF 0.919 BUT NO DIMENSION DATA (CODING ERROR?)


Setup and sample selection

### load data ------

    # Load HSE data
    hse_combined <- read.csv("./data/HSE_combined/hse_combined.csv")
    
    # IMD factor labels
    hse_combined$imd <- factor(hse_combined$imd,
                               labels=c("Least deprived",
                                        "Less deprived",
                                        "Median deprived",
                                        "More deprived",
                                        "Most deprived"))
    # IMD color scheme
    imd_cols =  rev(brewer.pal(5,"RdYlGn"))

Sample selection

    # remove years 2017 and 2018
    hse_combined = hse_combined[hse_combined$year <= 2014,]
    
    # remove NA's (for now)
    hse_combined = hse_combined[!is.na(hse_combined$eq5d),]
 
    # strata sample sizes 
    n_size_strata <- aggregate(eq5d~imd+age+sex,hse_combined,function(x)sum(!is.na(x)))
    
    ggplot(n_size_strata,aes(x=age,y=eq5d,col=as.factor(imd))) +
        geom_hline(yintercept = 100) +
        geom_hline(yintercept = 50) +
        geom_point(size=0.5,alpha=0.5) +
        geom_line(size=0.5,alpha=0.8) +
        ggtitle("Sample sizes") +
        scale_color_manual(values =  imd_cols,name="Deprivation") +
        ylab("Cases per strata") +
        facet_wrap(~sex) +
        theme(legend.position = "top")

    # remove age <16 bc no eq5d data (for now) 
    hse_combined <- hse_combined[hse_combined$age > 15, ]
    
    # set max age 75
    hse_combined$age[hse_combined$age>75] <- 75
    # n total: rows, cols
    dim(hse_combined)

mean eq5d over the lifespan by sex (years pooled)

Figure shows mean eq5d and 95% CI for the mean

    # mean eq5d over the lifespan by sex (years pooled) ------
    mean_lifespan_eq5d <- bootstrapci(hse_combined,"eq5d ~ age+sex",iterations = 100,print=F)
    
    # mean eq5d over lifetgime with 95%CI
    ggplot(mean_lifespan_eq5d, aes(x = age, y = eq5d, col = sex)) +
        geom_ribbon(aes(x=age,ymin=l95ci,ymax=u95ci,fill=sex),alpha=.2,size= 0.1) +
        geom_point() +
        geom_line() +
        ylab("Mean eq5d over lifetime and 95%CI intervalls") +
        theme_minimal()

FIGURE 1: mean eq5d by age and imd and sex (years pooled)

# fig 1: mean eq5d by age and imd and sex -------
    # mean eq5d over the lifespan by sex and imd (years pooled)
    lifespan_imd_eq5d <- aggregate(eq5d ~ age + sex + imd, hse_combined, mean)
    # head(lifespan_imd_eq5d)
    
    # strata-size
    strata_sizes_eq5d <- aggregate( eq5d ~ age+sex+imd,hse_combined, length)
    names(strata_sizes_eq5d)[4] = "strata_n"

# Figure 1 add on: 
    # eq5d score inequality over lifetime by sex
    df_imd1 = aggregate(eq5d ~ sex+age+imd,hse_combined[as.numeric(hse_combined$imd) == 1,],mean)
    names(df_imd1)[4] = "eq5d_1"
    df_imd5 = aggregate(eq5d ~ sex+age+imd,hse_combined[as.numeric(hse_combined$imd) == 5,],mean)
    names(df_imd5)[4] = "eq5d_5"
    df_imd_r = merge(df_imd1,df_imd5,by=c("sex","age"))
    df_imd_r$ineq_ratio = df_imd_r$eq5d_5/df_imd_r$eq5d_1
    df_imd_r$ineq_diff = df_imd_r$eq5d_5-df_imd_r$eq5d_1
    
    ggplot(df_imd_r,aes(x=age,y=ineq_ratio,col=sex)) +
        geom_point(size=0.5,alpha=0.5) +
        geom_line(size=0.5,alpha=0.5) +
        geom_smooth(se=F) +
        ylab("IMD 1 / IMD 5 eq5d ratio over lifetime by sex") +
        theme_minimal()

    # for females
    # mean + 95% CI for mean + strata size
    tbl_1_f_cis = bootstrapci(df = hse_combined[hse_combined$sex =="Female",],
                              formula = "eq5d ~ age_band + imd",
                              iterations = 100,
                              print = F)
    
    tbl_1_f_cis[,-c(1,2)] = round(tbl_1_f_cis[,-c(1:2)],3)
    tbl_1_f_cis$sample_n = formatC(tbl_1_f_cis$sample_n,digits = 0,format="f",big.mark = ",",)
    tbl_1_f_cis$eq5d = paste0(tbl_1_f_cis$eq5d," (",tbl_1_f_cis$l95ci,"-",tbl_1_f_cis$u95ci,") [",tbl_1_f_cis$sample_n,"]")
    tbl_1_f_cis = tbl_1_f_cis[,1:3]
    tbl_1_f_cis <- reshape(tbl_1_f_cis,idvar = "imd", timevar = "age_band", direction = "wide")
    tbl_1_f_cis$imd <- as.character(tbl_1_f_cis$imd)
    
    # inequality measures
    tbl_1_f <- aggregate(eq5d ~ age_band + imd, hse_combined[hse_combined$sex =="Female",], mean)
    tbl_1_f <- reshape(tbl_1_f,idvar = "imd", timevar = "age_band", direction = "wide")
    .temp_ratio = c("ratio", round( (tbl_1_f[1,-1] / tbl_1_f[5,-1])-1,2) )
    .temp_diff = c("diff",round( (tbl_1_f[1,-1] - tbl_1_f[5,-1]),2))
    names(.temp_ratio) =  names(.temp_diff ) = NULL
    tbl_1_f_cis <- rbind(tbl_1_f_cis,.temp_ratio,.temp_diff )
    kable(tbl_1_f_cis,caption = "Females")

TABLE 2: proprtion reporting any problems by imd and age and sex

# TABLE 2: % reporting any problems? --------
    
    dim_problem_ns_1 = aggregate(cbind(mo,sc,ua,pd,ad) ~  imd + sex  + age_band ,hse_combined,function(x){table(x)[1]})    
    dim_problem_ns_1[is.na(dim_problem_ns_1)] = 0
    names(dim_problem_ns_1)[4:8] = paste0(names(dim_problem_ns_1)[4:8],1)
    dim_problem_ns_2 = aggregate(cbind(mo,sc,ua,pd,ad) ~  imd + sex  + age_band ,hse_combined,function(x){table(x)[2]})    
    dim_problem_ns_2[is.na(dim_problem_ns_2)] = 0
    names(dim_problem_ns_2)[4:8] = paste0(names(dim_problem_ns_2)[4:8],2)
    dim_problem_ns_3 = aggregate(cbind(mo,sc,ua,pd,ad) ~  imd + sex  + age_band ,hse_combined,function(x){table(x)[3]})    
    dim_problem_ns_3[is.na(dim_problem_ns_3)] = 0
    names(dim_problem_ns_3)[4:8] = paste0(names(dim_problem_ns_3)[4:8],3)
    dim_problem_n = aggregate(cbind(mo) ~  imd + sex  + age_band ,hse_combined,function(x){length(x)})    
    names(dim_problem_n)[4] = "sample_n"
    
    
    dim_problems = merge(dim_problem_ns_1,dim_problem_ns_2)
    dim_problems = merge(dim_problems,dim_problem_ns_3)
    dim_problems = merge(dim_problems,dim_problem_n)
    
    
    dim_problems = dim_problems %>%
        mutate(mo_any = mo2+mo3,
               sc_any = sc2+sc3,
               ua_any = ua2+ua3,
               pd_any = pd2+pd3,
               ad_any = pd2+pd3) %>%
        mutate(mo_any_proz = round(mo_any/(mo1+mo_any),2),
               sc_any_proz = round(sc_any/(sc1+sc_any),2),
               ua_any_proz = round(ua_any/(ua1+ua_any),2),
               pd_any_proz = round(pd_any/(pd1+pd_any),2),
               ad_any_proz = round(ad_any/(ad1+ad_any),2)) %>%
        mutate(mo_3_proz = round(mo3/(mo1+mo_any),2),
               sc_3_proz = round(sc3/(sc1+sc_any),2),
               ua_3_proz = round(ua3/(ua1+ua_any),2),
               pd_3_proz = round(pd3/(pd1+pd_any),2),
               ad_3_proz = round(ad3/(ad1+ad_any),2))
    head(dim_problems)

    # TABLES 2.1 - 2.5 FEMALE
    dim_problems_tbl_f = with(dim_problems[dim_problems$sex=="Female",],
                              data.frame(imd,

    ##### PERCENT LEVELS STACKED AREAS
    dim_agg_o_1 = aggregate(cbind(mo,sc,ua,pd,ad) ~  imd + sex  + age ,hse_combined,function(x){table(x)[1]})
    dim_agg_o_3 = aggregate(cbind(mo,sc,ua,pd,ad) ~  imd + sex  + age ,hse_combined,function(x){table(x)[3]})
    dim_agg_o_2 = aggregate(cbind(mo,sc,ua,pd,ad) ~  imd + sex  + age ,hse_combined,function(x){table(x)[2]})
    dim_agg_o = merge(dim_agg_o_1,dim_agg_o_2,by=c("imd","sex","age"))
    dim_agg_o = merge(dim_agg_o,dim_agg_o_3,by=c("imd","sex","age"))
    level_labs = paste(rep(names(dim_agg_o_1)[4:8],times = 3), rep(c(1,2,3),each=5),sep="_") 
    names(dim_agg_o) = c("imd","sex","age",level_labs)

    # replace missings levels with 0
    dim_agg_o[is.na(dim_agg_o)] = 0
    dim_agg_o$dimension = NA
    head(dim_agg_o)

year effect on inequality?

Ratio of the mean eq5d indices of the least and most deprived quantile by age in different years (smoothened trend lines)

    # IMD 1 / IMD 5 RATIO over lifetime by year
    df_years_imd1 = aggregate(eq5d ~ year+age+imd,hse_combined[as.numeric(hse_combined$imd) == 1,],mean)
    names(df_years_imd1)[4] = "eq5d_1"
    df_years_imd5 = aggregate(eq5d ~ year+age+imd,hse_combined[as.numeric(hse_combined$imd) == 5,],mean)
    names(df_years_imd5)[4] = "eq5d_5"
    df_years_r = merge(df_years_imd1,df_years_imd5,by=c("year","age"))
    df_years_r$ineq_ratio = df_years_r$eq5d_1/df_years_r$eq5d_5-1
    
    ggplot(df_years_r,aes(x=age,y=ineq_ratio,col=(year),group=as.factor(year))) +
        geom_point(size=0.5,alpha=0.5) +
        geom_line(size=0.5,alpha=0.5) +
        geom_smooth(se=F) +
        scale_color_steps()+
        ylab("IMD 1 / IMD 5 eq5d ratio over lifetime by year") +
        theme_minimal()
